{"id":1254795414,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 1 week","timestamp":1715388374,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"6 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1254795414/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"44.7 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    int[] vals = {1, 5, 10, 50, 100, 500, 1000};\n    HashMap<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<Character, Integer>(7);\n    public Solution() {\n        map.put('I', 0);\n        map.put('V', 1);\n        map.put('X', 2);\n        map.put('L', 3);\n        map.put('C', 4);\n        map.put('D', 5);\n        map.put('M', 6);\n    }\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        int expected = 0;\n        int num = 0;\n        for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n            int curr = map.get(s.charAt(i));\n            if (curr >= expected) {\n                num += vals[curr];\n                expected = curr;\n            } else {\n                num -= vals[curr];\n            }\n        }\n        return num;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
